# ui-app extensions — append to _common/CLAUDE.md

## Skills (UI-specific additions)

| Skill | When |
|---|---|
| `ui-ux-pro-max` | Any UI structure / visual design / interaction decision. 99 UX guidelines, 161 color palettes, anti-patterns. |
| `design-system` | Three-layer token architecture (primitive → semantic → component). |
| `design` | Brand identity, design tokens, UI styling. |
| `onboarding-psychologist` | First-use flows. IDENTITY-TO-HABIT arc backed by behavioral research. |
| `frontend-design` (official plugin) | Frontend design companion. |
| `cc-skill-frontend-patterns` | Frontend code patterns. |

## UX discipline

Every user-facing surface follows `docs/UX_CONTRACT.md`. The contract gates UI PRs — they cite which sections they comply with.

Rule zero: **Attention → Question → Commitment → Feedback → Reveal**. The student / user must commit to a decision before the system reveals structure. No auto-advance, no answer-before-input.

## Accessibility — non-negotiable

- Color contrast ≥ 4.5:1 normal, ≥ 3:1 large.
- Focus rings visible on every interactive element.
- Aria labels on icon-only buttons.
- Keyboard navigation matches visual order.
- `prefers-reduced-motion` respected.
- Minimum 44×44px touch targets, 8px+ spacing.
